{%- endif %}
```

## Prerequisites

- [Azure CLI](https://learn.microsoft.com/cli/azure/install-azure-cli) >= 2.64
- An Azure subscription with **Contributor** + **User Access Administrator** roles
- Bicep CLI (bundled with Azure CLI 2.20+)

## Quick start

```bash
az login

# Validate templates first
task infra:validate

# Preview changes (what-if)
task infra:what-if:dev

# Deploy a single environment
task infra:deploy:dev

# Deploy using the helper script directly
zsh infra/scripts/deploy.azcli -p "{{ project_slug }}" -e dev

# Or via az deployment sub create
az deployment sub create \
  --location {{ azure_location }} \
  --template-file infra/deploy.bicep \
  --parameters infra/parameters/dev/deploy.dev.bicepparam \
  --parameters projectName="{{ project_slug }}" env="dev"
```

## Environments

| Environment | Parameter file                                  | Purpose              | Safety prompt |
| ----------- | ----------------------------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------- |
| dev         | `parameters/dev/deploy.dev.bicepparam`          | Development          | No            |
| test        | `parameters/test/deploy.test.bicepparam`        | Automated testing    | No            |
| staging     | `parameters/staging/deploy.staging.bicepparam`  | Pre-production       | Yes           |
| prod        | `parameters/prod/deploy.prod.bicepparam`        | Production           | Yes           |

## Task commands

All infrastructure tasks are namespaced under `infra:` in go-task:

### Validation

```bash
task infra:validate          # Validate all Bicep templates
task infra:validate:deploy   # Validate deploy.bicep only
task infra:validate:main     # Validate main.bicep only
```

### What-if (preview changes)

```bash
task infra:what-if:dev
task infra:what-if:test
task infra:what-if:staging
task infra:what-if:prod
```

### Deploy (subscription-scoped)

```bash
task infra:deploy:dev        # No confirmation
task infra:deploy:test       # No confirmation
task infra:deploy:staging    # Prompts for confirmation
task infra:deploy:prod       # Prompts for confirmation
```

### Deploy (resource-group-scoped only)

```bash
task infra:deploy:rg:dev
task infra:deploy:rg:test
task infra:deploy:rg:staging
task infra:deploy:rg:prod
```

### Resource inspection

```bash
task infra:resources:list    # List resources across all environments
task infra:resources:groups  # List all resource groups
```
{% if secret_backend == "azure_kv" %}

### Key Vault operations

```bash
task infra:kv:add-secret VAULT=my-vault NAME=my-secret VALUE=my-value
task infra:kv:add-user VAULT=my-vault UPN=user@example.com
task infra:kv:list VAULT=my-vault
```
{% endif %}

### Cleanup

```bash
task infra:clean             # Delete ALL resource groups (prompts for confirmation)
```

## Deploy script

The `scripts/deploy.azcli` script supports three modes:

```bash
# Single environment
zsh infra/scripts/deploy.azcli -p "{{ project_slug }}" -e dev

# Default: dev + prod
zsh infra/scripts/deploy.azcli -p "{{ project_slug }}"

# All four environments
zsh infra/scripts/deploy.azcli -p "{{ project_slug }}" --all
```
{%- if database_backend in ("postgresql", "azure_postgresql") %}

## Database backup

The `scripts/backup-db.zsh` script creates a compressed `pg_dump` backup:

```bash
zsh infra/scripts/backup-db.zsh                  # backs up to ./backups/
zsh infra/scripts/backup-db.zsh /path/to/dir     # custom backup directory
```

Set connection details via environment variables (`POSTGRES_HOST`, `POSTGRES_PORT`,
`POSTGRES_DB`, `POSTGRES_USER`) or source them from the project `.env` file.
{%- endif %}

## Module conventions

Each module follows the **claim_handler** convention:

| Convention          | Description                                                     |
| ------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `namePrefix`        | Project-level naming prefix (e.g., `myapp-dev`)                 |
| `enabled`           | Boolean flag to conditionally skip resource creation             |
| Parameterised objects | All tuneable settings passed as typed object parameters         |
| `commonTags`        | Standard tags (`project`, `environment`) applied to all resources |
| Optional name       | Each module accepts an optional explicit name override           |
